text: Utrecht University (Dutch: Universiteit Utrecht), shortened to UU, is a public university in Utrecht, a city in the province of Utrecht, the Netherlands. Utrecht University was established in 1636 (its predecessor in 1634). It has about 32,000 students. Its focus is on all sorts of sciences. == Other websites == * Category:1636 establishments Category:Colleges and universities in the Netherlands Category:Utrecht (city) Category:17th-century establishments in the Netherlands Category:1630s establishments in Europe
